Mmm. That's disappointing because, as Hippo asserts, it turns the SCP into an anomaly which simply punishes wrongdoing. From a characterization standpoint, it's much more interesting to have the leech anomaly be too vigorous in its crusade than to be perfect at its job - and because the topic being handled is child sexual abuse, which goes unnoticed and unpunished far too often, the article becomes, in a very, very perverse way, a sort of wish-fulfillment article (the wish being for child predators to face justice).





